 1840-1940 by historian W.W. Knox (pdf)]\n\n{{Public housing in the United Kingdom}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Council House}}\n[[Category:House types]]\n[[Category:Public housing in the United Kingdom| ]]\n[[Category:Housing in the United Kingdom]]\n", "name_user": "WisDom-UK", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Public_housing_in_the_United_Kingdom"}
{"title_page": "R\u00e9sidence Herron", "text_new": "'''R\u00e9sidence Herron''', also known as '''CHSLD Herron''', is a privately-owned senior's residence in [[Dorval]], [[Quebec]]. The property was acquired by [[Katasa Groupe]] in 2015.<ref name=\"2020-04-11-BIU-CP\">{{cite news |title=Quebec premier says 31 people have died at troubled long-term care home |url=https://www.bowenislandundercurrent.com/covid-19/quebec-premier-says-31-people-have-died-at-troubled-long-term-care-home-1.24116470 |accessdate=11 April 2020 |work=Bowen Island Undercurrent |agency=The Canadian Press |date=11 April 2020}}</ref> During the 2020 COVID-19 pandemic, most staff abandoned the facility, leading to a police investigation and government takeover of the facility. Conditions were described by health officials as similar to \"a concentration camp.\"\n\n==COVID-19 deaths, facility desertion==\n\nBetween March 13 and April 11, 31 residents of the facility died; as of April 11, five were confirmed to be a result of COVID-19.<ref name=\"2020-04-11-MG-confirms\">{{cite news |last1=Feith |first1=Jesse |title=COVID-19: Premier Legault confirms 31 dead at Dorval care residence |url=https://montrealgazette.com/news/local-news/covid-19-premier-legault-confirms-31-dead-at-dorval-care-residence/ |accessdate=11 April 2020 |work=Montreal Gazette |date=11 April 2020 |location=Montreal QC}}</ref> The facility averaged fourth deaths a month,<ref name=\"2020-04-10-MG-find-bodies\">{{cite news |last1=Derfel |first1=Aaron |title=Public health, police find bodies, feces at Dorval seniors\u2019 residence: sources |url=https://montrealgazette.com/news/local-news/public-health-police-find-bodies-feces-at-dorval-seniors-residence-sources/wcm/19011f52-7b04-41c4-a674-93bc26283749/ |accessdate=11 April 2020 |work=Montreal Gazette |date=10 April 2020 |location=Montreal QC}}</ref>\nand had claimed only two deaths during the period.<ref name=\"2020-04-10-MG-find-bodies\" /> The first known COVID death was in a patient sent to [[Jewish General Hospital]] on March 26, dying shortly after.<ref name=\"2020-04-11-updates\">{{cite news |last1=Curtis |first1=Christopher |title=Coronavirus updates: 31 dead at Herron seniors' residence, Legault says |url=https://montrealgazette.com/news/local-news/coronavirus-updates-fears-about-school-re-opening-legault-to-brief-reporters/wcm/62b7a033-57c6-49bf-84ea-0c0ede4de23b/ |accessdate=11 April 2020 |work=Montreal Gazette |date=11 April 2020 |location=Montreal QC}}</ref> Health authorities found that the facility was found to be \"deserted\" of staff, as of March 29, three days after the first death.<ref name=\"2020-04-11-BIU-CP\" />\n\nLe Centre int\u00e9gr\u00e9 universitaire de sant\u00e9 et de services sociaux de l'Ouest-de-l'\u00cele-de-Montr\u00e9al took over the facility.<ref name=\"2020-04-11-updates\" />\n\nOn April 10, a team of nurses rescued residents. Minister of Health and Social Services [[Danielle McCann]] then knew of only 18 deaths, two of which are linked to COVID-19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lapresse.ca/covid-19/202004/11/01-5268926-film-dhorreur-dans-un-chsld.php|title=\u00abFilm d\u2019horreur\u00bb dans un CHSLD|date=2020-04-11|website=La Presse|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> According to the health professionals who intervened in the residence, the living conditions inside were similar to \"a concentration camp\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://montrealgazette.com/news/local-news/public-health-police-find-bodies-feces-at-dorval-seniors-residence-sources|title=Public health, police find bodies, feces at Dorval seniors\u2019 residence: sources|website=Montreal Gazette|language=en-CA|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>.\n\nOn April 11, Quebec Premier [[Fran\u00e7ois Legault]] promised a criminal investigation into the facility. The Premier says that, after COVID, the province would hold a larger review of private and public seniors' residences.<ref name=\"2020-04-11-MG-confirms\" /> The Canadian federal government also promised additional measures for long-term care facilities, that day.<ref name=\"2020-04-11-BIU-CP\" />\n\n==See also==\n* [https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Centre_int%C3%A9gr%C3%A9_de_sant%C3%A9_et_de_services_sociaux Centre int\u00e9gr\u00e9 de sant\u00e9 et de services sociaux] on French Wikipedia\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|https://chsldherron.com/}} {{dead link}}\n\n[[Category:Nursing homes in Canada]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Canada]]\n", "text_old": "'''R\u00e9sidence Herron''', also known as '''CHSLD Herron''', is a privately-owned senior's residence in [[Dorval]], [[Quebec]]. The property was acquired by [[Katasa Groupe]] in 2015.<ref name=\"2020-04-11-BIU-CP\">{{cite news |title=Quebec premier says 31 people have died at troubled long-term care home |url=https://www.bowenislandundercurrent.com/covid-19/quebec-premier-says-31-people-have-died-at-troubled-long-term-care-home-1.24116470 |accessdate=11 April 2020 |work=Bowen Island Undercurrent |agency=The Canadian Press |date=11 April 2020}}</ref> During the 2020 COVID-19 pandemic, most staff abandoned the facility, leading to a police investigation and government takeover of the facility. Conditions were described by health officials as similar to \"a concentration camp.\"\n\n==COVID-19 deaths, facility desertion==\n\nBetween March 13 and April 11, 31 residents of the facility died; as of April 11, five were confirmed to be a result of COVID-19.<ref name=\"2020-04-11-MG-confirms\">{{cite news |last1=Feith |first1=Jesse |title=COVID-19: Premier Legault confirms 31 dead at Dorval care residence |url=https://montrealgazette.com/news/local-news/covid-19-premier-legault-confirms-31-dead-at-dorval-care-residence/ |accessdate=11 April 2020 |work=Montreal Gazette |date=11 April 2020 |location=Montreal QC}}</ref> The facility averaged fourth deaths a month,<ref name=\"2020-04-10-MG-find-bodies\">{{cite news |last1=Derfel |first1=Aaron |title=Public health, police find bodies, feces at Dorval seniors\u2019 residence: sources |url=https://montrealgazette.com/news/local-news/public-health-police-find-bodies-feces-at-dorval-seniors-residence-sources/wcm/19011f52-7b04-41c4-a674-93bc26283749/ |accessdate=11 April 2020 |work=Montreal Gazette |date=10 April 2020 |location=Montreal QC}}</ref>\nand had claimed only two deaths during the period.<ref name=\"2020-04-10-MG-find-bodies\" /> The first known COVID death was in a patient sent to [[Jewish General Hospital]] on March 26, dying shortly after.<ref name=\"2020-04-11-updates\">{{cite news |last1=Curtis |first1=Christopher |title=Coronavirus updates: 31 dead at Herron seniors' residence, Legault says |url=https://montrealgazette.com/news/local-news/coronavirus-updates-fears-about-school-re-opening-legault-to-brief-reporters/wcm/62b7a033-57c6-49bf-84ea-0c0ede4de23b/ |accessdate=11 April 2020 |work=Montreal Gazette |date=11 April 2020 |location=Montreal QC}}</ref> Health authorities found that the facility was found to be \"deserted\" of staff, as of March 29, three days after the first death.<ref name=\"2020-04-11-BIU-CP\" />\n\nLe Centre int\u00e9gr\u00e9 universitaire de sant\u00e9 et de services sociaux de l'Ouest-de-l'\u00cele-de-Montr\u00e9al took over the facility.<ref name=\"2020-04-11-updates\" />\n\nOn April 10, a team of nurses rescued residents. Minister of Health and Social Services Danielle McCann then knew of only 18 deaths, two of which are linked to COVID-19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lapresse.ca/covid-19/202004/11/01-5268926-film-dhorreur-dans-un-chsld.php|title=\u00abFilm d\u2019horreur\u00bb dans un CHSLD|date=2020-04-11|website=La Presse|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> According to the health professionals who intervened in the residence, the living conditions inside were similar to \"a concentration camp\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://montrealgazette.com/news/local-news/public-health-police-find-bodies-feces-at-dorval-seniors-residence-sources|title=Public health, police find bodies, feces at Dorval seniors\u2019 residence: sources|website=Montreal Gazette|language=en-CA|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>.\n\nOn April 11, Quebec Premier Fran\u00e7ois Legault promised a criminal investigation into the facility. The Premier says that, after COVID, the province would hold a larger review of private and public seniors' residences.<ref name=\"2020-04-11-MG-confirms\" /> The Canadian federal government also promised additional measures for long-term care facilities, that day.<ref name=\"2020-04-11-BIU-CP\" />\n\n==See also==\n* [https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Centre_int%C3%A9gr%C3%A9_de_sant%C3%A9_et_de_services_sociaux Centre int\u00e9gr\u00e9 de sant\u00e9 et de services sociaux] on French Wikipedia\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|https://chsldherron.com/}} {{dead link}}\n\n[[Category:Nursing homes in Canada]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Canada]]\n", "name_user": "Zanimum", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCOVID-19 deaths, facility desertion", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/R%C3%A9sidence_Herron"}
